# RTK - Rust Token Killer (Cline)

**Usage**: Token-optimized CLI proxy for shell commands.

## Rule

Always prefix shell commands with `rtk` to minimize token consumption.

Examples:

```bash
rtk git status
rtk cargo test
rtk ls src/
rtk grep "pattern" src/
rtk find "*.rs" .
rtk docker ps
rtk gh pr list
```

## Meta Commands

```bash
rtk gain              # Show token savings
rtk gain --history    # Command history with savings
rtk discover          # Find missed RTK opportunities
rtk proxy <cmd>       # Run raw (no filtering, for debugging)
```

## Why

RTK filters and compresses command output before it reaches the LLM context, saving 60-90% tokens on common operations. Always use `rtk <cmd>` instead of raw commands.

---

# Caveman Ecosystem (JuliusBrussee)

## caveman - Output Compression (~75% fewer tokens)

**Installed for Continue**. Also works with: Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, Windsurf, Cline, Copilot, etc.

```bash
/caveman [lite|full|ultra|wenyan]  # Compress agent replies
/caveman-commit                     # Conventional commits, ≤50 char subject
/caveman-review                     # One-line PR comments
/caveman-stats                      # Token usage + lifetime savings + USD
/caveman-compress <file>            # Rewrite memory files (CLAUDE.md) in caveman-speak
caveman-shrink                      # MCP middleware for any MCP server
```

**Trigger**: Say "talk like caveman" or run `/caveman`. Stop with "normal mode".

## cavemem - Cross-Agent Persistent Memory

**Installed via npx**. Compresses observations with caveman grammar (~75% fewer tokens), stores in local SQLite, retrieves via MCP.

```bash
cavemem install --ide cline         # Install for Cline
cavemem status                      # Wiring + DB counts + embedding backfill
cavemem viewer                      # Open http://127.0.0.1:37777
cavemem search <query>              # Search memory (BM25 + cosine re-rank)
cavemem compress <file>             # Compress file with caveman grammar
cavemem reindex                     # Rebuild FTS5 + vector index
cavemem export <out.jsonl>          # Dump observations
cavemem mcp                         # Start MCP server (stdio)
```

**Settings**: `~/.cavemem/settings.json` (compression intensity, embedding provider, search blend, privacy patterns)

## caveman-code - Whole Terminal Agent (~2× fewer tokens than Codex)

```bash
npm install -g @juliusbrussee/caveman-code
```

